1. How to setup local dev environment

Get the latest 1.6 sdk and adjust your PATH:
export JAVA_HOME=$JAVA6_HOME; export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH

Git to go
Follow below step to setup git ssh public key: http://help.github.com/linux-set-up-git/
on windows, you can consider the Git client: http://code.google.com/p/tortoisegit/
make sure Line Endings will be handled correctly: git config --global core.autocrlf true

install Maven 3
Download Maven 3.0.3 from http://maven.apache.org/download.html
Unzip the contents in your root Maven folder. Setup M2_HOME in your environment variables and point it to your installation directory. 
(Note: You need to use M2_HOME instead of M3_HOME because the maven plugin for eclipse will not work with M3_HOME.)
Add ‘%M2_HOME%/bin’ to your PATH variable. Open a command window and run the ‘mvn -version’ command. You should see version information about Maven 3.0.3

Download Eclipse J2EE Indigo Distribution:
eclipse-jee-indigo-SR1-win32.zip

install eclipse git plugin EGit:
http://download.eclipse.org/egit/updates-nightly

install eclipse maven2 plugin M2Eclipse:
http://download.eclipse.org/technology/m2e/releases

Get the source code
git clone git@github.com:archibald2012/toolkit.git

Import to Eclipse
File-->Import-->Import Existing Maven Project into Workspace







